---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
---

<Layout title="About | Luis Castro" description="About Luis Castro.">
  <section class="space-y-8">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-muted-foreground">Static page</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl leading-none">About</h1>
      <p class="text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        This page is static content, so you can edit it directly whenever you want to update your
        bio, work, or current interests.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-8 text-muted-foreground">
      <p>
        Write your introduction here. This can be a short bio, what you work on, and what people
        should expect to find on the site.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can also use this space for a small now section, links, or a concise explanation of
        what belongs in posts, dailies, and the library.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
